---
description: no dynamic imports - always use static imports at the top of the file
globs: *.tsx, *.ts
---

- never use inline imports in type annotations like `import('module').Type`
- never use dynamic imports like `await import('module')` or
  `const x = await import('module')`
- always import types and modules at the top of the file using standard import
  statements
- prefer
  `import type { Subscription } from '@coursebuilder/core/schemas/subscription'`
  over inline `import('@coursebuilder/core/schemas/subscription').Subscription`
- if you think you need dynamic imports for code splitting, use Next.js
  `dynamic()` instead
